INSERT INTO `locales_source` VALUES ('2919','','default','Category %category has been saved.','','none'),('2920','','default','You cannot send more than %limit messages in @interval. Try again later.','','none'),('2921','','default','Contact @username','','7.26'),('2922','','default','%sender-name (@sender-from) sent an e-mail regarding %category.','','none'),('2923','','default','%sender-name (@sender-from) sent %recipient-name an e-mail.','','none'),('2924','','default','The Contact module allows visitors to contact site administrators and other users. Users specify a subject, write their message, and can have a copy of their message sent to their own e-mail address. For more information, see the online handbook entry for <a href="@contact">Contact module</a>.','','7.41'),('2925','','default','User contact forms','','7.41'),('2926','','default','Site users can be contacted with a user contact form that keeps their e-mail address private. Users may enable or disable their personal contact forms by editing their <em>My account</em> page. If enabled, a <em>Contact</em> tab leads to a personal contact form displayed on their user profile. Site administrators are still able to use the contact form, even if has been disabled. The <em>Contact</em> tab is not shown when you view your own profile.','','7.41'),('2927','','default','Site-wide contact forms','','7.41'),('2928','','default','The <a href="@contact">Contact page</a> provides a simple form for users with the <em>Use the site-wide contact form</em> permission to send comments, feedback, or other requests. You can create categories for directing the contact form messages to a set of defined recipients. Common categories for a business site, for example, might include "Website feedback" (messages are forwarded to website administrators) and "Product information" (messages are forwarded to members of the sales department). E-mail addresses defined within a category are not displayed publicly.','','7.41'),('2929','','default','When the site-wide contact form is enabled, a link in the main <em>Navigation</em> menu is created, but the link is disabled by default. This menu link can be enabled on the <a href=''@menu''>Menus administration page</a>.','','7.41');
INSERT INTO `locales_source` VALUES ('2930','','default','Customization','','7.41'),('2931','','default','If you would like additional text to appear on the site-wide or personal contact page, use a block. You can create and edit blocks on the <a href="@blocks">Blocks administration page</a>.','','7.41'),('2932','','default','Add one or more categories on this page to set up your site-wide <a href="@form">contact form</a>.','','none'),('2933','','default','A <em>Contact</em> menu item (disabled by default) is added to the Navigation menu, which you can modify on the <a href="@menu-settings">Menus administration page</a>.','','none'),('2934','','default','If you would like additional text to appear on the site-wide contact page, use a block. You can create and edit blocks on the <a href="@blocks">Blocks administration page</a>.','','none'),('2935','','default','Administer contact forms and contact form settings','','7.41'),('2936','','default','Use the site-wide contact form','','7.41'),('2937','','default','Use users'' personal contact forms','','7.41'),('2938','','default','!sender-name (!sender-url) sent a message using the contact form at !form-url.','','none'),('2939','','default','[!site-name] !subject','','7.26'),('2940','','default','!sender-name (!sender-url) has sent you a message via your contact form (!form-url) at !site-name.','','7.26'),('2941','','default','If you don''t want to receive such e-mails, you can change your settings at !recipient-edit-url.','','7.26'),('2942','','default','Allow other users to contact you via a <a href="@url">personal contact form</a> which keeps your e-mail address hidden. Note that some privileged users such as site administrators are still able to contact you even if you choose to disable this feature.','','7.41'),('2943','','default','Enable the personal contact form by default for new users.','','7.41'),('2944','','default','Changing this setting will not affect existing users.','','7.41'),('2945','','default','The Contextual links module displays links related to regions of pages on your site to users with <em>access contextual links</em> permission. For more information, see the online handbook entry for <a href="@contextual">Contextual links module</a>.','','7.41');
INSERT INTO `locales_source` VALUES ('2946','','default','Displaying contextual links','','7.41'),('2947','','default','Contextual links are supplied by modules, to give you quick access to tasks associated with regions of pages on your site. For instance, if you have a custom menu block displayed in a sidebar of your site, the Blocks and Menus modules will supply links to configure the block and edit the menu. The Contextual links module collects these links into a list for display by your theme, and also adds JavaScript code to the page to hide the links initially, and display them when your mouse hovers over the block.','','7.41'),('2948','','default','Use contextual links','','7.41'),('2949','','default','Use contextual links to perform actions related to elements on a page.','','7.41'),('2950','','default','Contextual links','','none'),('2951','','default','Provides contextual links to perform actions related to elements on a page.','','7.41'),('2952','','default','Tracking user activity','','7.41'),('2953','','default','By enabling blocks such as <em>Who''s online</em> and <em>Who''s new</em>, site users can track who is logged in and new user signups at a centralized location.','','7.41'),('2954','','default','Tracking content activity','','7.41'),('2955','','default','By enabling blocks such as <em>Recent blog posts</em>, <em>New forum topics</em> and <em>Recent comments</em>, site users can view newly added site content at a glance.','','7.41'),('2956','','default','View the administrative dashboard','','7.41'),('2957','','default','This dashboard region is empty. Click <em>Customize dashboard</em> to add blocks to it.','','7.23'),('2958','','default','DRAG HERE','','7.23'),('2959','','default','Provides a dashboard page in the administrative interface for organizing administrative tasks and tracking information within your site.','','7.41'),('2960','; modules/dashboard/dashboard.js','default','Customize dashboard','','7.41'),('2961','','default','Clear log messages','','7.41'),('2962','','default','This will permanently remove the log messages from the database.','','7.41');
INSERT INTO `locales_source` VALUES ('2963','','default','Database log cleared.','','none'),('2964','','default','The Database logging module logs system events in the Drupal database. For more information, see the online handbook entry for the <a href="@dblog">Database logging module</a>.','','7.41'),('2965','','default','Monitoring your site','','7.41'),('2966','','default','Debugging site problems','','7.41'),('2967','','default','Field validation errors','','7.22'),('2968','','default','Attempt to create a field with a name longer than 32 characters: %name','','none'),('2969','','default','Attempt to create field name %name which already exists and is active.','','none'),('2970','','default','Attempt to create field name %name which already exists, although it is inactive.','','none'),('2971','','default','Attempt to create field name %name which is reserved by entity type %type.','','none'),('2972','','default','Attempt to create a field of unknown type %type.','','none'),('2973','','default','Attempt to create a field with unknown storage type %type.','','none'),('2974','','default','Attempt to create an instance of field @field_name without a bundle.','','none'),('2975','','default','This field is required. ','','none'),('2976','','default','Enabling field types','','7.41'),('2977','','default','The Field module provides the infrastructure for fields and field attachment; the field types and input widgets themselves are provided by additional modules. Some of the modules are required; the optional modules can be enabled from the <a href="@modules">Modules administration page</a>. Drupal core includes the following field type modules: Number (required), Text (required), List (required), Taxonomy (optional), Image (optional), and File (optional); the required Options module provides input widgets for other field modules. Additional fields and widgets may be provided by contributed modules, which you can find in the <a href="@contrib">contributed module section of Drupal.org</a>. Currently enabled field and input widget modules:','','7.41');
INSERT INTO `locales_source` VALUES ('2978','','default','Managing field data storage','','7.41'),('2979','','default','Developers of field modules can either use the default <a href="@sql-store">Field SQL storage module</a> to store data for their fields, or a contributed or custom module developed using the <a href="@storage-api">field storage API</a>.','','7.41'),('2980','','default','The Field SQL storage module stores field data in the database. It is the default field storage module; other field storage mechanisms may be available as contributed modules. See the <a href="@field-help">Field module help page</a> for more information about fields.','','7.41'),('2981','','default','Default SQL storage','','7.41'),('2982','','default','Stores fields in the local SQL database, using per-field tables.','','7.41'),('2983','','default','Field SQL storage','','none'),('2984','','default','Stores field data in an SQL database.','','7.41'),('2985','','default','The List module defines various fields for storing a list of items, for use with the Field module. Usually these items are entered through a select list, checkboxes, or radio buttons. See the <a href="@field-help">Field module help page</a> for more information about fields.','','7.41'),('2986','','default','This field stores simple on/off or yes/no options.','','7.41'),('2987','','default','List (text)','','7.41'),('2988','','default','The ''checkboxes/radio buttons'' widget will display checkboxes if the <em>Number of values</em> option is greater than 1 for this field, otherwise radios will be displayed.','','none'),('2989','','default','Allowed HTML tags in labels: @tags','','none'),('2990','','default','The value of this field is being determined by the %function function and may not be changed.','','none'),('2991','','default','Allowed values list: each key must be a valid integer or decimal.','','none'),('2992','','default','Allowed values list: each key must be a string at most 255 characters long.','','none'),('2993','','default','Allowed values list: keys must be integers.','','none'),('2994','','default','Defines list field types. Use with Options to create selection lists.','','7.41');
INSERT INTO `locales_source` VALUES ('2995','','default','The Number module defines various numeric field types for the Field module. Numbers can be in integer, decimal, or floating-point form, and they can be formatted when displayed. Number fields can be limited to a specific set of input values or to a range of values. See the <a href="@field-help">Field module help page</a> for more information about fields.','','7.41'),('2996','','default','This field stores a number in the database as an integer.','','7.41'),('2997','','default','This field stores a number in the database in a fixed decimal format.','','7.41'),('2998','','default','This field stores a number in the database in a floating point format.','','7.41'),('2999','','default','The minimum value that should be allowed in this field. Leave blank for no minimum.','','7.23'),('3000','','default','The maximum value that should be allowed in this field. Leave blank for no maximum.','','7.23'),('3001','','default','Define a string that should be prefixed to the value, like ''$ '' or ''&euro; ''. Leave blank for none. Separate singular and plural values with a pipe (''pound|pounds'').','','7.23'),('3002','','default','Only numbers and the decimal separator (@separator) allowed in %field.','','none'),('3003','','default','The Options module defines checkbox, selection, and other input widgets for the Field module. See the <a href="@field-help">Field module help page</a> for more information about fields.','','7.41'),('3004','','default','The Text module defines various text field types for the Field module. A text field may contain plain text only, or optionally, may use Drupal''s <a href=''@filter-help''>text filters</a> to securely manage HTML output. Text input fields may be either a single line (text field), multiple lines (text area), or for greater input control, a select box, checkbox, or radio buttons. If desired, the field can be validated, so that it is limited to a set of allowed values. See the <a href=''@field-help''>Field module help page</a> for more information about fields.','','7.41');
