INSERT INTO `locales_source` VALUES ('8445','/html/drupal7/Sauvages_PACA_dev/admin/config/user-interface/custom-breadcrumbs?render=overlay','default','Add a custom-breadcrumbs-home ID attribute to the home breadcrumb item.','','7.22'),('8446','/html/drupal7/Sauvages_PACA_dev/admin/config/user-interface/custom-breadcrumbs?render=overlay','default','Add a numbered class attribute for each breadcrumb item.','','7.22'),('8447','/html/drupal7/Sauvages_PACA_dev/admin/config/user-interface/custom-breadcrumbs?render=overlay','default','If enabled, a custom-breadcrumbs-item-N class attribute will be assigned for each item, where N designates the item number, starting with the first item after the home breadcrumb.','','7.22'),('8448','/html/drupal7/Sauvages_PACA_dev/admin/config/user-interface/custom-breadcrumbs?render=overlay','default','Add even and odd classes to breadcrumb items.','','7.22'),('8449','/html/drupal7/Sauvages_PACA_dev/admin/config/user-interface/custom-breadcrumbs?render=overlay','default','Store an identifier for breadcrumb theming.','','7.22'),('8450','/html/drupal7/Sauvages_PACA_dev/admin/config/user-interface/custom-breadcrumbs?render=overlay','default','If enabled, the breadcrumb class ''custom-breadcrumbs-<em>type</em>'' (where <em>type</em> is the breadcrumb type) can be retrieved and used in the breadcrumb theme override. The function <strong>custom_breadcrumbs_unique_breadcrumb_id()</strong> will return a string containing the class name.','','7.22'),('8451','/html/drupal7/Sauvages_PACA_dev/admin/config/user-interface/custom-breadcrumbs?render=overlay','default','Append a unique breadcrumb id number to the custom-breadcrumbs-<em>type</em> identifier.','','7.22'),('8452','/html/drupal7/Sauvages_PACA_dev/admin/config/user-interface/custom-breadcrumbs?render=overlay','default','If this option and ''Store an identifier for breadcrumb theming'' are both enabled, the identifer will be custom-breadcrumbs-<em>type</em>-<em>id</em>, where id is the unique br