INSERT INTO `locales_source` VALUES ('9460','/admin/modules?render=overlay','default','CKEditor for Drupal 7 Documentation','','7.41'),('9461','/admin/modules?render=overlay','default','Plugins: Code Snippet and MathJax','','7.41'),('9462','/admin/modules?render=overlay','default','Code Snippet and MathJax are special plugins for CKEditor that are using external JavaScript libraries to style content inside editing area. The result that is returned by CKEditor is just an HTML tag that needs to again processed by a filter (either server side or client side) in order to display it properly to the user.','','7.41'),('9463','/admin/modules?render=overlay','default','MathJax (Mathematical Formulas)','','7.41'),('9464','/admin/modules?render=overlay','default','With mathjax plugin, CKEditor produces LaTeX code surrounded by !code. In order to have it properly rendered on your site you might need to add !mathjax on your website, the simplest way to do this is to add this to your theme: !script','','7.41'),('9465','/admin/modules?render=overlay','default','Code Snippet','','7.41'),('9466','/admin/modules?render=overlay','default','With codesnippet plugin, CKEditor produces code snippets surrounded by !code. <strong>Note:</strong> You might need to add !highlight on your website so that the displayed code was rendered nicely as in CKEditor. The simplest way to do this is to add this to your theme: !script','','7.41'),('9467','/admin/config/content/ckeditor?render=overlay','default','Plugin for inserting files from IMCE without image dialog','','7.41'),('9468','/admin/config/content/ckeditor/editg?render=overlay','default','The path to CKEditor (the WYSIWYG rich text editor downloaded from !ckeditorcom). Provide a path relative to the document root, unless CKEditor is located on an external URL. In such case enter the full URL to a folder with CKEditor.<br />The simplest way to have the editor running is to use CDN, to use it set: !cdn','','7.41'),('9469','/admin/config/conten